WEBVTT

1
00:00:28.165 --> 00:00:30.845
God! I love this job! Man!
Can't you go any faster?

2
00:00:31.085 --> 00:00:32.085
Floor this thing!

3
00:00:32.285 --> 00:00:34.645
It's my wife's. I won't go faster.

4
00:00:34.845 --> 00:00:36.125
You're doing 65 now.

5
00:00:36.325 --> 00:00:37.845
65?! Shit!

6
00:00:38.125 --> 00:00:40.845
Get your foot off the pedal!
You're killing my corn!

7
00:00:43.525 --> 00:00:48.446
We're eastbound on 4th, in pursuit of
a red BMW, driver Caucasian, blonde.

8
00:00:48.806 --> 00:00:51.206
Plate 2-Boy-Adam-Henry-174.

9
00:00:53.046 --> 00:00:56.366
You are westbound on 2nd.
20 William 12 is southbound.

10
00:00:56.686 --> 00:00:59.966
You're heading straight
toward each other.

11
00:01:00.206 --> 00:01:02.366
- Somebody back off.
- Got it.

12
00:01:02.646 --> 00:01:05.046
- What'd she say?
- We're about to have an accident.

13
00:01:24.206 --> 00:01:28.207
Go! We'll stick with the red bastard.
You chase the blue.

14
00:01:28.487 --> 00:01:32.167
That's confirmed.
You got red, we'll get blue.

15
00:01:32.407 --> 00:01:36.487
- What's the pursuit?
- 20 William 15 and 20 William 12.

16
00:01:37.087 --> 00:01:39.047
- That's Riggs, Murtaugh.
- And their squad.

17
00:01:39.247 --> 00:01:41.727
- $20 on Riggs and Murtaugh.
- Who's driving?

18
00:01:41.927 --> 00:01:43.527
Murtaugh, in his wife's wagon.

19
00:01:43.727 --> 00:01:46.727
I knew nothing about the wagon.
Bet's off.

20
00:01:47.007 --> 00:01:48.167
Shut up!

21
00:01:57.527 --> 00:01:58.887
What the hell is that?

22
00:01:59.087 --> 00:02:01.527
What fuckin' language is that?

23
00:02:01.768 --> 00:02:03.008
It's German.

24
00:02:03.248 --> 00:02:04.368
Japanese?

25
00:02:04.608 --> 00:02:07.608
It's a Japanese radio.
Maybe they bought the L.A.P.D.

26
00:02:07.888 --> 00:02:08.928
They own everything.

27
00:02:14.728 --> 00:02:16.128
Shotgun!

28
00:02:24.968 --> 00:02:26.728
Shots are being fired.

29
00:02:27.288 --> 00:02:28.968
Thanks for the scoop.

30
00:02:29.288 --> 00:02:31.768
The bastard shot my wife's windshield.

31
00:02:32.128 --> 00:02:33.448
Entering the pursuit.

32
00:02:46.809 --> 00:02:49.609
Oh, shit, man! We're splitting up!

33
00:02:53.929 --> 00:02:56.249
Son-of-a-bitch! Now we're cooking.

34
00:03:00.289 --> 00:03:01.249
Step on it!

35
00:03:14.329 --> 00:03:15.449
Look out!

36
00:03:22.530 --> 00:03:23.690
See you!

37
00:03:44.810 --> 00:03:47.730
I'd like to see your license
and proof of insurance!

38
00:04:03.371 --> 00:04:05.891
We got one. Yours is going up the hill.

39
00:04:06.091 --> 00:04:07.411
So is Riggs, on foot!

40
00:04:11.251 --> 00:04:14.211
Hey, Riggs! Get your slow ass in here!

41
00:04:14.571 --> 00:04:16.211
Get in here, now!

42
00:04:16.571 --> 00:04:17.691
Only if I drive.

43
00:04:17.891 --> 00:04:19.531
Move over. I'll drive.

44
00:04:19.731 --> 00:04:22.091
No, go around. I'm driving.

45
00:04:22.331 --> 00:04:24.331
I'll drive.

46
00:04:25.411 --> 00:04:27.411
Did you get a make on that red Beemer?

47
00:04:28.171 --> 00:04:29.691
Not one scratch, you hear?

48
00:04:34.852 --> 00:04:36.492
- You won't make it.
- I will.

49
00:04:36.692 --> 00:04:37.892
There's not enough room!

50
00:04:38.212 --> 00:04:39.852
You're not going to make it!

51
00:04:40.932 --> 00:04:42.932
Look at my side panel!

52
00:04:53.372 --> 00:04:55.772
Goddamn it, you were right.

53
00:04:56.292 --> 00:04:58.212
There wasn't enough room.

54
00:06:00.934 --> 00:06:02.294
He's turning right!

55
00:06:11.614 --> 00:06:12.934
Get out of the way!

56
00:06:28.295 --> 00:06:29.855
This was a new car, Riggs.

57
00:06:30.295 --> 00:06:31.455
Well, it still is.

58
00:06:38.975 --> 00:06:40.135
On three.

59
00:06:40.815 --> 00:06:41.895
One...

60
00:06:42.535 --> 00:06:44.375
...two... three!

61
00:06:45.895 --> 00:06:47.215
Shit!

62
00:06:48.815 --> 00:06:50.735
You forgot to turn your indicator on.

63
00:06:50.975 --> 00:06:53.615
Where the hell is he?
This guy's Mandrake!

64
00:06:53.815 --> 00:06:56.735
Where were you, man?!
Goddamnit!

65
00:06:57.015 --> 00:06:58.455
Me?! Where did he go?!

66
00:06:58.655 --> 00:07:01.336
- He's fucking gone!
- I can see that!

67
00:07:01.576 --> 00:07:04.536
- You're supposed to come on "three".
- I thought you meant, "three" then go!

68
00:07:04.736 --> 00:07:06.536
No! We always go on "three"!

69
00:07:06.736 --> 00:07:09.736
Sometimes we go, "one, two, three,"
then go!

70
00:07:11.056 --> 00:07:12.336
Go check back there!

71
00:07:12.576 --> 00:07:16.576
If you see anybody running out,
just pump the shit out of them.

72
00:07:17.536 --> 00:07:18.936
What was that?

73
00:07:20.856 --> 00:07:23.336
- He crawled into the trunk.
- I got you covered.

74
00:07:29.936 --> 00:07:31.576
Holy Christ!

75
00:07:32.216 --> 00:07:33.696
That's a lot of money.

76
00:07:40.217 --> 00:07:41.857
It's gold!

77
00:07:42.457 --> 00:07:43.617
Gold!

78
00:07:43.897 --> 00:07:45.017
Krugerrands.

79
00:07:45.217 --> 00:07:48.057
It's illegal. You can't import them
into the country.

80
00:07:48.377 --> 00:07:49.497
You're right.

81
00:07:49.737 --> 00:07:53.297
The damage you caused is coming
out of the department's budget.

82
00:07:53.577 --> 00:07:57.537
- Pay it in Krugerrands.
- Don't make jokes, make arrests.

83
00:07:57.817 --> 00:07:59.737
I want an explanation.

84
00:08:00.017 --> 00:08:03.737
- Things got out of hand.
- You said this was a routine bust.

85
00:08:04.017 --> 00:08:08.897
You didn't mention helicopters,
automatic weapons, Krugerrands...

86
00:08:09.257 --> 00:08:11.217
This was bigger than we thought.

87
00:08:11.737 --> 00:08:13.057
Talk to you later.

88
00:08:19.578 --> 00:08:22.578
I worked psycho ward.
You'll never get out.

89
00:08:23.938 --> 00:08:26.258
One minute, fifteen seconds.

90
00:08:26.578 --> 00:08:28.418
Shapiro, scratch my nose.

91
00:08:29.778 --> 00:08:34.378
Hey! What's going on? Is this
kindergarten or a police station?

92
00:08:34.858 --> 00:08:36.258
Get some work done.

93
00:08:36.938 --> 00:08:39.578
Houdini Jr. Bets he can free himself
in 5 minutes.

94
00:08:39.858 --> 00:08:40.858
I will too.

95
00:08:46.098 --> 00:08:48.178
Don't try this at home, kids.

96
00:08:58.139 --> 00:09:02.579
It's over now. Put your money
on the desk and get back to work.

97
00:09:04.899 --> 00:09:06.299
Suckers.

98
00:09:12.539 --> 00:09:14.739
How the hell did you do that?

99
00:09:16.299 --> 00:09:20.099
I dislocated my shoulder once.
Now I can do it whenever I want.

100
00:09:20.299 --> 00:09:21.739
Doesn't it hurt?

101
00:09:22.099 --> 00:09:23.979
Yeah, it does.

102
00:09:24.739 --> 00:09:27.659
But not as much as...
when I put it back in.

103
00:09:38.940 --> 00:09:40.860
If it isn't Mrs. Sigmund Fraud.

104
00:09:41.340 --> 00:09:43.500
My door is always open, Sergeant.

105
00:09:44.780 --> 00:09:48.340
We should keep this
on a professional level.

106
00:09:49.500 --> 00:09:52.340
Why the hell do you
do this to yourself?

107
00:09:52.620 --> 00:09:55.500
Who else could I do it to?
None of them will let me.

108
00:09:55.780 --> 00:09:57.260
And I need the money.

109
00:09:57.460 --> 00:09:58.340
Cough up!

110
00:10:01.020 --> 00:10:03.860
It's not all here yet. I want it all.

111
00:10:11.021 --> 00:10:12.981
Where did this come from?

112
00:10:13.701 --> 00:10:18.541
You can't help yourself to this stuff!
It's evidence. It's a Krugerrand.

113
00:10:19.021 --> 00:10:21.461
- It's mine. I won it.
- It's not yours.

114
00:10:21.821 --> 00:10:23.821
You want to get busted?

115
00:10:25.541 --> 00:10:27.541
Want to get something to eat?

116
00:10:27.821 --> 00:10:29.301
Not tonight.

117
00:10:29.661 --> 00:10:31.981
- Rianne's commercial is on.
- She's in a commercial?

118
00:10:32.221 --> 00:10:33.861
Not so loud!

119
00:10:34.061 --> 00:10:36.901
What's wrong?
I'd be proud if I was you.

120
00:10:37.741 --> 00:10:40.901
I haven't seen it yet.
What if she stinks?

121
00:10:41.181 --> 00:10:43.661
You got to be kidding. She'll be great.

122
00:10:43.981 --> 00:10:44.982
Listen up!

123
00:10:46.182 --> 00:10:48.222
Tonight at... what time?

124
00:10:48.582 --> 00:10:49.422
Come on!

125
00:10:49.742 --> 00:10:51.062
What time?

126
00:10:51.902 --> 00:10:52.782
Eight.

127
00:10:53.062 --> 00:10:54.662
Eight o'clock, on... channel?

128
00:10:57.182 --> 00:11:01.342
Eight. The Sergeant's daughter, Rianne.
Here's a picture of her.

129
00:11:03.022 --> 00:11:06.182
She's going to make
her television debut in a commercial.

130
00:11:12.702 --> 00:11:15.542
With this crowd, baby,
you'd better not stink.

131
00:11:30.783 --> 00:11:34.263
What happened? This is a new car.
Mom's going to be upset!

132
00:11:34.543 --> 00:11:37.223
- It's still new.
- No, it's not, it's wrecked.

133
00:11:37.463 --> 00:11:39.903
I don't want your mother to know.

134
00:11:41.063 --> 00:11:42.903
Do your homework too.

135
00:11:43.143 --> 00:11:46.023
- Hey! I haven't read these.
- Rianne put them there.

136
00:11:46.223 --> 00:11:48.463
Why don't you look out for me?

137
00:11:48.743 --> 00:11:52.823
Hey, Ricky! I want to use my driveway
once in a while.

138
00:11:53.423 --> 00:11:55.263
Nice oxygen tent.

139
00:11:55.463 --> 00:11:58.903
- Do I look like Michael Jackson?
- No, but you're bad.

140
00:11:59.263 --> 00:12:03.464
This is a two-car garage,
and this is my hobby room upstairs.

141
00:12:03.744 --> 00:12:08.224
I retire when I'm 52, the whole
nine yards kick in when I'm 55.

142
00:12:08.504 --> 00:12:10.304
You're not retiring, are you?

143
00:12:10.584 --> 00:12:13.424
- I've thought of it, since I met you.
- Thank you.

144
00:12:13.744 --> 00:12:17.184
This is a nice hobby room.
All you need now is a hobby.

145
00:12:20.344 --> 00:12:21.104
Jesus!

146
00:12:21.584 --> 00:12:22.944
What's wrong with you?

147
00:12:23.824 --> 00:12:25.704
I'm sorry. That's very uncool.

148
00:12:25.944 --> 00:12:28.184
You're sorry? Check my shorts!

149
00:12:28.944 --> 00:12:31.424
- Don't you use hammers anymore?
- What's a hammer?

150
00:12:33.264 --> 00:12:36.784
Easy. It's no Saturday Night Special,
for crying out loud.

151
00:12:38.625 --> 00:12:40.105
Give it back.

152
00:12:42.225 --> 00:12:44.265
A man's not even safe in his own home.

153
00:12:44.545 --> 00:12:46.105
Then stay the hell out of here.

154
00:12:46.945 --> 00:12:48.625
You got any traffic warrants?

155
00:12:48.905 --> 00:12:50.105
Can you fix them?

156
00:12:57.305 --> 00:12:59.625
Almost time. Are we taping this?

157
00:12:59.905 --> 00:13:02.825
Yes, so we can watch it
over and over again.

158
00:13:03.065 --> 00:13:04.425
Take the stairs.

159
00:13:04.625 --> 00:13:07.785
Nick, get your feet off the table.
You too, Martin.

160
00:13:07.985 --> 00:13:10.985
- The color's no good.
- It's fine. You'll mess it up.

161
00:13:11.265 --> 00:13:12.705
I want you to look good.

162
00:13:12.905 --> 00:13:13.785
Unplug it.

163
00:13:13.825 --> 00:13:15.066
That's your sister!

164
00:13:15.506 --> 00:13:16.706
Picture's perfect.

165
00:13:16.906 --> 00:13:17.906
Yeah?

166
00:13:19.186 --> 00:13:20.106
Do I know you?

167
00:13:20.746 --> 00:13:21.786
Yes, sir.

168
00:13:21.986 --> 00:13:24.506
We had a long talk about a week ago.

169
00:13:24.746 --> 00:13:25.826
About what?

170
00:13:26.106 --> 00:13:27.666
Your new hobby room.

171
00:13:27.946 --> 00:13:29.586
This is George.

172
00:13:32.506 --> 00:13:34.426
Did you sense that I liked you?

173
00:13:35.626 --> 00:13:36.786
Yes, sir.

174
00:13:37.666 --> 00:13:39.426
Sit down and be quiet.

175
00:13:42.786 --> 00:13:45.946
- What are you eating?
- My tuna fish sandwich.

176
00:13:46.186 --> 00:13:47.106
Tuna?

177
00:13:47.706 --> 00:13:49.506
You can't eat tuna!

178
00:13:49.946 --> 00:13:51.426
Dad killed Flipper.

179
00:13:51.626 --> 00:13:53.267
We're boycotting tuna...

180
00:13:53.547 --> 00:13:57.507
...because they kill the dolphins
that get caught in the nets.

181
00:13:58.147 --> 00:13:59.227
Have ham.

182
00:13:59.467 --> 00:14:00.747
Eat Miss Piggy.

183
00:14:01.867 --> 00:14:04.187
- I'm sorry!
- It's only my eye.

184
00:14:09.147 --> 00:14:11.147
Oh, my God! It's coming on!

185
00:14:13.987 --> 00:14:15.227
My baby!

186
00:14:16.307 --> 00:14:18.827
Don't she look gorgeous, Martin?

187
00:14:27.707 --> 00:14:29.348
When the time has come...

188
00:14:30.068 --> 00:14:32.068
...and the moment is right...

189
00:14:33.068 --> 00:14:34.228
...remember...

190
00:14:34.748 --> 00:14:37.068
...use Ramses' Extra condoms.

191
00:14:38.628 --> 00:14:40.428
- We do!
- Ramses' Extra.

192
00:14:41.188 --> 00:14:44.428
Because caring means
all the protection you can get.

193
00:14:53.748 --> 00:14:55.228
Take the kids upstairs.

194
00:14:56.148 --> 00:14:57.908
We learn this in Human Development.

195
00:14:58.188 --> 00:15:00.828
In Human what?!
Human Development what?!

196
00:15:01.028 --> 00:15:02.508
Chill out, Daddy.

197
00:15:02.748 --> 00:15:04.108
Upstairs!

198
00:15:04.348 --> 00:15:05.868
Nick, upstairs.

199
00:15:06.388 --> 00:15:08.549
You know how your father is.

200
00:15:08.789 --> 00:15:11.349
- I looked fat.
- I liked you.

201
00:15:13.629 --> 00:15:14.989
Home. Out!

202
00:15:15.789 --> 00:15:16.829
I got a gun.

203
00:15:22.269 --> 00:15:24.629
What? She looked beautiful.

204
00:15:24.869 --> 00:15:28.229
I liked it. She made me want to buy
rubbers right now.

205
00:15:35.389 --> 00:15:38.549
I thought it was great.
Rianne, that was...

206
00:15:39.469 --> 00:15:41.789
- I thought you were terrific.
- Really?

207
00:15:42.069 --> 00:15:44.310
I think she's got a hell of a future.

208
00:15:45.070 --> 00:15:46.910
George is afraid. He's going home.

209
00:15:47.150 --> 00:15:48.350
Stick around.

210
00:15:48.750 --> 00:15:50.150
He has a gun.

211
00:15:50.430 --> 00:15:53.590
It's an old gun
and he's not a very good shot.

212
00:15:54.430 --> 00:15:56.990
That's good. I'm going anyway.
Good night.

213
00:15:57.270 --> 00:15:59.870
- I'll buy you a beer.
- You let him buy it.

214
00:16:00.110 --> 00:16:03.070
You're under 21. Be back by midnight.

215
00:16:04.310 --> 00:16:06.670
Wait and see. Cops never let up.

216
00:16:06.950 --> 00:16:10.910
I'll have rubbers on my desk,
rubbers in the mail, in the coffee...

217
00:16:11.150 --> 00:16:15.590
If you'd only kept your mouth shut!
I'm going for a walk.

218
00:16:15.830 --> 00:16:18.830
Give the boys some credit.
In one ear, out the rubber.

219
00:16:31.831 --> 00:16:34.151
How goes it with you, Hans?

220
00:16:34.351 --> 00:16:36.511
Okay. You, Pieter?

221
00:16:37.511 --> 00:16:40.471
That's quite enough of that.
Come on over here, Hans.

222
00:16:42.511 --> 00:16:45.511
Mind the plastic.
I'm having painting done.

223
00:16:46.831 --> 00:16:48.591
The important thing is...

224
00:16:48.831 --> 00:16:49.831
...are you okay?

225
00:16:50.191 --> 00:16:51.991
No bones broken?

226
00:16:52.511 --> 00:16:53.831
I'm fine, thanks.

227
00:16:54.591 --> 00:16:56.031
Just bumps and bruises, eh?

228
00:16:56.671 --> 00:16:58.031
Yeah, that's all.

229
00:16:58.271 --> 00:16:59.632
Good, good.

230
00:17:03.192 --> 00:17:06.152
However, we lost over $1 million
in Krugerrand.

231
00:17:07.512 --> 00:17:10.672
I know. I'm sorry, Mr. Rudd.

232
00:17:11.312 --> 00:17:12.512
It happens.

233
00:17:12.872 --> 00:17:14.712
It's not your fault.

234
00:17:15.032 --> 00:17:18.032
Sometimes things do not go as planned.

235
00:17:18.872 --> 00:17:22.312
As you say, they just happen,
Eh, Pieter?

236
00:17:30.472 --> 00:17:33.632
You give a whole new meaning
to the word, "drop cloth. "

237
00:17:35.312 --> 00:17:38.633
Certain policemen have become
an intolerable nuisance.

238
00:17:39.233 --> 00:17:43.713
They are obviously on to us again.
How do you propose to handle it?

239
00:17:44.073 --> 00:17:45.393
Warn them off.

240
00:17:47.233 --> 00:17:48.913
It's my experience...

241
00:17:49.353 --> 00:17:52.673
...that a scared cop
is more useful than a dead one.

242
00:17:52.913 --> 00:17:54.073
A warning?

243
00:17:54.673 --> 00:17:56.393
Is that not a bit tame?

244
00:17:56.833 --> 00:17:58.233
Depends on how you do it.

245
00:18:00.233 --> 00:18:02.153
Then you better look at this.

246
00:18:08.593 --> 00:18:11.913
This is the policeman in charge.

247
00:18:14.514 --> 00:18:15.714
A Kaffir.

248
00:18:17.434 --> 00:18:18.594
Lovely.

249
00:18:19.754 --> 00:18:21.394
Remember to take these in order.

250
00:18:22.274 --> 00:18:25.114
There's a packet
for each day of the week.

251
00:18:27.034 --> 00:18:28.434
This yours?

252
00:18:29.114 --> 00:18:30.794
I found it in the wash.

253
00:18:37.394 --> 00:18:38.954
I keep losing this.

254
00:18:40.114 --> 00:18:41.354
Something's wrong.

255
00:18:41.714 --> 00:18:45.114
No, not really.
It's just a goddamn pen.

256
00:18:48.074 --> 00:18:49.434
What about the pen?

257
00:18:49.954 --> 00:18:51.795
It reminds me of something.

258
00:18:52.795 --> 00:18:54.035
Of what?

259
00:18:54.635 --> 00:18:56.315
It reminds me of...

260
00:18:56.635 --> 00:18:58.475
...the night Vicki was killed.

261
00:18:59.635 --> 00:19:01.075
I didn't mean to push.

262
00:19:02.475 --> 00:19:05.275
That's okay.
We never really talked about this.

263
00:19:10.315 --> 00:19:14.795
I was to meet her for dinner.
One of those romantic dinners for two.

264
00:19:15.075 --> 00:19:16.275
I had so much work.

265
00:19:18.755 --> 00:19:20.555
And I forgot about it.

266
00:19:22.155 --> 00:19:26.315
She waited at the restaurant
for an hour before she drove home.

267
00:19:28.116 --> 00:19:32.276
It was midnight when I got home
to a ringing phone. I answered it.

268
00:19:32.516 --> 00:19:34.996
They said she was killed in a car crash.

269
00:19:40.516 --> 00:19:43.516
If I'd been driving,
we'd have been all right.

270
00:19:46.196 --> 00:19:50.196
I remember falling down
on my knees and shaking all over.

271
00:19:50.516 --> 00:19:53.196
I remember thinking, "I'm losing it. "

272
00:19:54.356 --> 00:19:56.716
There I was lying on the floor...

273
00:19:58.196 --> 00:20:02.236
...and I'm seeing under the couch,
and I see this gold pen.

274
00:20:03.636 --> 00:20:08.357
Just lying there. I'd been looking
for it for two months. There it is.

275
00:20:10.197 --> 00:20:12.197
She wasn't a great housekeeper.

276
00:20:13.877 --> 00:20:17.597
This voice goes off in my head,
like a drill instructor.

277
00:20:18.557 --> 00:20:20.877
It said, "Get up! Now!"

278
00:20:22.397 --> 00:20:26.717
I didn't feel like it, but I got up.
Muscles were still working.

279
00:20:27.237 --> 00:20:29.677
Then I drove to the hospital...

280
00:20:29.997 --> 00:20:33.157
...identified her, signed her out
with my gold pen.

281
00:20:33.397 --> 00:20:35.717
Trish found a gold pen in the laundry.

282
00:20:45.918 --> 00:20:48.078
Look around you, Sam.

283
00:20:49.758 --> 00:20:51.238
One day, Sam...

284
00:20:52.278 --> 00:20:53.918
...this'll all be yours.

285
00:20:57.518 --> 00:21:00.598
Find a nice bitch,
raise a couple of pups.

286
00:21:01.438 --> 00:21:03.758
A man could be happy here.

287
00:21:07.958 --> 00:21:11.918
Anybody tell you if you sit on
cold rocks too long, you get piles?

288
00:21:12.198 --> 00:21:13.798
Let's go watch TV.

289
00:22:42.961 --> 00:22:44.201
Kaffirs!

290
00:22:47.721 --> 00:22:49.281
Wondering about your kids?

291
00:22:50.361 --> 00:22:52.521
About what we've done to them?

292
00:22:53.481 --> 00:22:56.001
If I was you, I'd be going nuts now.

293
00:22:57.161 --> 00:22:59.321
I'd be going fucking bananas.

294
00:23:00.401 --> 00:23:02.041
Want to know what we've done?

295
00:23:02.641 --> 00:23:03.521
Shall I tell you?

296
00:23:05.561 --> 00:23:08.281
Just let your imagination run wild.

297
00:23:09.001 --> 00:23:10.921
This has just been a warning.

298
00:23:11.241 --> 00:23:14.882
After this, it gets bloody.
Tell your people to back off.

299
00:23:15.242 --> 00:23:17.002
Don't be a smart Kaffir.

300
00:23:17.562 --> 00:23:19.242
Maybe we let you live, huh?

301
00:23:40.082 --> 00:23:43.082
- You didn't see a face?
- Not one. They had on hoods.

302
00:23:43.442 --> 00:23:44.722
What about a voice?

303
00:23:44.922 --> 00:23:49.442
That crazy motherfucker who did talk
had a strange accent.

304
00:23:49.763 --> 00:23:54.443
Not German, not English.
Kind of guttural. Really shitty accent.

305
00:23:54.723 --> 00:23:58.043
Wait. Anything like what we chased
the other night?

306
00:23:58.443 --> 00:24:00.763
Yeah, kind of like that.

307
00:24:01.123 --> 00:24:02.603
Trish and the kids?

308
00:24:02.803 --> 00:24:05.723
They're at her sister's house
in Bellflower.

309
00:24:05.963 --> 00:24:10.123
Listen up! You heard what happened
to Rog last night?

310
00:24:10.643 --> 00:24:12.603
Forensics get back with anything?

311
00:24:12.883 --> 00:24:14.883
Not yet. They'll keep us posted.

312
00:24:15.243 --> 00:24:18.563
We got to watch each other's
backs and fronts.

313
00:24:18.803 --> 00:24:22.643
You can all watch my back
in poker tomorrow. You in?

314
00:24:22.923 --> 00:24:25.723
- If we catch these assholes.
- Count me in.

315
00:24:31.484 --> 00:24:33.964
I got something special for you.

316
00:24:34.324 --> 00:24:37.324
Leo Getz has been placed
in protective custody.

317
00:24:37.604 --> 00:24:41.244
You guys are going to baby-sit
until Washington sends the Feds.

318
00:24:41.604 --> 00:24:44.804
- How long?
- Until the red tape is processed.

319
00:24:44.884 --> 00:24:46.244
Couple, three days.

320
00:24:46.484 --> 00:24:50.644
Getz is going to testify
before a commission of inquiry.

321
00:24:50.924 --> 00:24:52.924
Drugs, laundered money, etc.

322
00:24:53.484 --> 00:24:54.404
I'll be there in 10 minutes.

323
00:24:57.004 --> 00:24:58.684
This is not a shit assignment.

324
00:24:59.004 --> 00:25:00.844
- Yes, it is.
- No, it isn't.

325
00:25:01.284 --> 00:25:02.004
It isn't.

326
00:25:02.324 --> 00:25:03.204
It is.

327
00:25:03.524 --> 00:25:05.365
Shut up, both of you.

328
00:25:06.445 --> 00:25:08.125
I've guaranteed his safety.

329
00:25:08.365 --> 00:25:09.204
Why us?

330
00:25:09.205 --> 00:25:12.365
You two are the most qualified. And...

331
00:25:12.645 --> 00:25:15.605
...after last night,
you could use the break.

332
00:25:15.845 --> 00:25:17.125
I can handle last night.

333
00:25:18.285 --> 00:25:19.645
What do we do with him?

334
00:25:19.845 --> 00:25:21.365
Take him to Disneyland.

335
00:25:22.205 --> 00:25:24.125
This stinks. This stinks.

336
00:25:24.365 --> 00:25:28.845
I don't give a fuck! I don't have an
ulcer because I know when to say that.

337
00:25:29.125 --> 00:25:30.645
Here's where he's staying.

338
00:25:30.885 --> 00:25:35.165
A nice hotel. The Justice Department
is paying. Enjoy yourselves.

339
00:25:36.285 --> 00:25:37.645
One more thing.

340
00:25:40.565 --> 00:25:41.685
Know what that says?

341
00:25:42.046 --> 00:25:44.726
Yeah. Same thing as that,
but I don't give a fuck.

342
00:25:48.726 --> 00:25:51.406
You're lucky.
I have to live with that.

343
00:26:02.726 --> 00:26:04.286
What room is that for?

344
00:26:04.646 --> 00:26:05.486
612.

345
00:26:08.166 --> 00:26:10.126
This is it. 612.

346
00:26:13.486 --> 00:26:14.766
Police.

347
00:26:15.006 --> 00:26:16.126
How do I know that?

348
00:26:16.606 --> 00:26:20.007
After I shoot you, you can
examine the bullet. Open up.

349
00:26:21.927 --> 00:26:24.087
Don't you want to see a badge?

350
00:26:24.327 --> 00:26:25.807
- Where's your badge?
- Shut up.

351
00:26:26.007 --> 00:26:28.327
I get it. Bad cop, good cop.

352
00:26:28.607 --> 00:26:29.927
Shut up.

353
00:26:31.167 --> 00:26:33.607
Bad cop, bad cop.
I know the routines.

354
00:26:33.847 --> 00:26:36.767
- Are you Leo Getz?
- That's me, Leo Getz.

355
00:26:37.007 --> 00:26:40.487
Whatever you need, Leo gets. Get it?

356
00:26:41.007 --> 00:26:43.847
I use that to break the ice
when I meet people.

357
00:26:44.127 --> 00:26:46.247
I'm Sgt. Murtaugh, this is Sgt. Riggs.

358
00:26:46.447 --> 00:26:49.367
Nice to meet you.
So what do I call you guys?

359
00:26:49.607 --> 00:26:50.927
Sgt. Murtaugh and Sgt. Riggs.

360
00:26:51.127 --> 00:26:52.967
We're going to be your shadow.

361
00:26:55.127 --> 00:26:57.128
That's fine. Hey, an old-fashioned...

362
00:26:58.648 --> 00:27:01.688
Okay. I just ain't seen one
in a long time.

363
00:27:01.968 --> 00:27:04.288
I didn't think anyone used them anymore.

364
00:27:04.888 --> 00:27:08.048
I bet the kid's got an automatic.
Have you?

365
00:27:08.328 --> 00:27:09.368
Yep, a Beretta.

366
00:27:11.728 --> 00:27:13.168
You sure you guys are cops?

367
00:27:14.168 --> 00:27:17.008
Better watch how you treat me.
I'm a state witness.

368
00:27:17.248 --> 00:27:18.528
Star witness.

369
00:27:19.568 --> 00:27:21.128
We'll take that room.

370
00:27:22.048 --> 00:27:24.488
I already have my stuff in this room.

371
00:27:32.248 --> 00:27:36.409
It's yours, okay?
I'll move it in the small room.

372
00:27:36.729 --> 00:27:40.089
I'm the smallest guy here.
I'll take the small room.

373
00:27:40.409 --> 00:27:44.569
Hey, loosen up, guys!
We're going to be together a long time.

374
00:27:45.489 --> 00:27:46.249
I'll get it.

375
00:27:47.769 --> 00:27:49.329
It's only room service.

376
00:27:50.089 --> 00:27:52.929
You hungry? I'll call
for anything you want.

377
00:27:53.209 --> 00:27:55.009
See this silk robe? Free.

378
00:27:55.689 --> 00:27:57.409
- It's not free.
- Yes, it is.

379
00:27:57.689 --> 00:28:00.689
- It's taxpayers' money.
- Same thing.

380
00:28:04.449 --> 00:28:05.769
Morning, gentlemen.

381
00:28:09.769 --> 00:28:13.450
That's my food. You guys
didn't want anything. Bring it here.

382
00:28:14.290 --> 00:28:15.450
It's mine.

383
00:28:16.290 --> 00:28:18.050
You could have had something.

384
00:28:19.290 --> 00:28:21.050
I ordered eggs, not hamburger.

385
00:28:27.210 --> 00:28:28.690
Not the window!

386
00:28:31.610 --> 00:28:32.610
Shit!

387
00:28:58.331 --> 00:28:59.811
Where is that son-of-a-bitch?

388
00:29:01.611 --> 00:29:04.371
Somebody stop that guy! Stop him!

389
00:29:06.171 --> 00:29:09.011
Don't leave me! I can't swim!

390
00:29:15.171 --> 00:29:19.771
We're near the edge of the pool.
Now get the fuck off my back!

391
00:29:20.171 --> 00:29:22.491
Clear! Get back! Police!

392
00:29:23.851 --> 00:29:24.811
You okay?

393
00:29:25.011 --> 00:29:27.692
Where were you?
Why didn't you follow me?

394
00:29:27.972 --> 00:29:30.212
- Yeah, why didn't you?
- I was 7 floors up!

395
00:29:32.132 --> 00:29:33.532
- He hit me.
- Good!

396
00:29:36.012 --> 00:29:40.972
This guy took a big chance to pop all of
us. What'd you witness, a murder?

397
00:29:41.212 --> 00:29:43.252
Nothing like that. Honest.

398
00:29:45.852 --> 00:29:50.292
All I did was launder a half a billion
dollars in drug money.

399
00:29:51.372 --> 00:29:53.372
Half a billion dollars?!

400
00:29:53.692 --> 00:29:57.212
More or less.
Who can count that much money?

401
00:29:57.532 --> 00:30:00.932
Could I have some cotton balls
for my nose?

402
00:30:01.372 --> 00:30:03.052
Could you shut the fuck up?

403
00:30:03.733 --> 00:30:05.373
You're supposed to take care of me.

404
00:30:05.733 --> 00:30:06.573
Shut up!

405
00:30:07.893 --> 00:30:11.373
Mr. Getz got away.
Our best opportunity and he gets away.

406
00:30:11.733 --> 00:30:16.213
He slips through our fingers
and into the hands of the police.

407
00:30:17.053 --> 00:30:18.333
What are you doing?

408
00:30:19.253 --> 00:30:22.573
Checking to see
if I was standing on plastic.

409
00:30:23.413 --> 00:30:25.053
Okay, I got it.

410
00:30:25.893 --> 00:30:29.253
I'm who I am. You're a drug dealer.
I work in a bank.

411
00:30:29.573 --> 00:30:32.213
You have money to launder.
What do you do?

412
00:30:32.413 --> 00:30:33.733
Bring it to you.

413
00:30:35.173 --> 00:30:38.093
- He does.
- I don't understand. Why me?

414
00:30:38.373 --> 00:30:39.693
Who am I?

415
00:30:41.694 --> 00:30:44.094
You're a courier. You work for him.

416
00:30:44.374 --> 00:30:45.694
I'm the drug dealer.

417
00:30:49.254 --> 00:30:52.854
Don't you have plates? What is this?

418
00:30:55.014 --> 00:30:59.534
I deposit the cash into the account
of a dummy finance company.

419
00:31:00.774 --> 00:31:02.214
I issue you a cashier's check...

420
00:31:02.774 --> 00:31:06.614
...in his name,
minus a small commission for myself.

421
00:31:07.374 --> 00:31:08.574
- The other end.
- You like breathing?

422
00:31:08.774 --> 00:31:09.774
How much?

423
00:31:10.054 --> 00:31:11.094
2%.

424
00:31:11.774 --> 00:31:14.294
Not bad, Leo. Pretty prosperous.

425
00:31:16.814 --> 00:31:19.975
You return it to me as collateral
on a loan I make to you.

426
00:31:20.295 --> 00:31:23.775
But you don't pay back the loan.
You keep the money.

427
00:31:24.055 --> 00:31:25.055
How's that work?

428
00:31:25.415 --> 00:31:27.815
That's it! Don't you get it?

429
00:31:28.135 --> 00:31:31.975
It's your money. You don't pay it back.
And it's clean.

430
00:31:32.295 --> 00:31:34.495
It is now laundered.

431
00:31:35.975 --> 00:31:37.815
You cops aren't too bright.

432
00:31:39.975 --> 00:31:42.135
This is the best part.

433
00:31:42.815 --> 00:31:45.655
You take a tax deduction...

434
00:31:46.255 --> 00:31:49.575
...on interest payments
you don't even make.

435
00:31:51.095 --> 00:31:53.335
- Am I a genius?
- You're a swindler.

436
00:31:53.615 --> 00:31:54.575
Cheat.

437
00:31:55.015 --> 00:31:56.216
Come on!

438
00:31:56.856 --> 00:32:00.816
Everyone cheats. Look at the Pentagon.
So you got it?

439
00:32:02.856 --> 00:32:05.776
So how come you turned yourself in,
Mr. Big Shot?

440
00:32:06.336 --> 00:32:08.576
I was scamming those guys for months.

441
00:32:09.016 --> 00:32:11.016
Every transaction, I kept a little.

442
00:32:11.296 --> 00:32:12.096
You?

443
00:32:12.696 --> 00:32:14.856
It was easy. Cash deposits...

444
00:32:15.136 --> 00:32:18.456
...millions of dollars in small bills
changing hands.

445
00:32:18.696 --> 00:32:21.736
Who's going to miss $10,000 here,
$20,000 there?

446
00:32:22.616 --> 00:32:23.336
Drug dealers.

447
00:32:24.696 --> 00:32:26.376
That's right. They did.

448
00:32:26.696 --> 00:32:29.296
That's why I'm living
out of a suitcase now.

449
00:32:31.856 --> 00:32:33.457
You can give that to Nick.

450
00:32:34.217 --> 00:32:37.217
But it's softer.
I put a fabric softener in there.

451
00:32:37.497 --> 00:32:38.497
It's small, Leroy.

452
00:32:38.697 --> 00:32:42.897
It's Leo, not Leroy.
I'll buy you another shirt.

453
00:32:43.137 --> 00:32:45.897
Just give me the names
of those drug dealers.

454
00:32:46.137 --> 00:32:47.817
I don't know any.

455
00:32:48.057 --> 00:32:50.057
I just dealt with the couriers.

456
00:32:50.337 --> 00:32:52.177
Where does Trish keep my laundry?

457
00:32:52.377 --> 00:32:54.217
Behind the machine.

458
00:32:55.737 --> 00:32:58.057
You never met anyone except couriers?

459
00:32:59.577 --> 00:33:01.177
No names.

460
00:33:04.417 --> 00:33:08.897
Wait a minute, come to think of it!
Okay, listen.

461
00:33:09.257 --> 00:33:12.738
They took me up in the hills
to a house on stilts.

462
00:33:13.258 --> 00:33:16.258
And I had a job interview with a guy...

463
00:33:16.538 --> 00:33:18.498
...and his name was...

464
00:33:19.418 --> 00:33:20.898
Haynes! Hans!

465
00:33:21.178 --> 00:33:23.418
- Take us there.
- We have to sit on this guy.

466
00:33:23.778 --> 00:33:25.578
It won't hurt to look.

467
00:33:25.938 --> 00:33:26.858
I know the address.

468
00:33:27.058 --> 00:33:27.818
Let's go.

469
00:33:28.098 --> 00:33:29.098
We shouldn't do this!

470
00:33:29.538 --> 00:33:31.418
Come on, don't be a killjoy!

471
00:33:31.778 --> 00:33:34.258
We're back! You're black, I'm mad.

472
00:33:34.458 --> 00:33:36.098
This is going to be great!

473
00:33:36.458 --> 00:33:39.258
If we're going, shouldn't I have a gun?

474
00:33:41.938 --> 00:33:44.258
Is my nose still bleeding?
It's really sore.

475
00:33:44.538 --> 00:33:46.218
Sorry about that.

476
00:33:50.819 --> 00:33:52.659
It should be coming up soon.

477
00:33:53.059 --> 00:33:55.379
- 9856.
- That's it.

478
00:33:55.659 --> 00:33:59.059
- That's another possibility.
- This is the ninth possibility, Leo.

479
00:33:59.339 --> 00:34:02.379
That's it. Nine.
My lucky number. Nine.

480
00:34:02.659 --> 00:34:04.659
Stay in the car.

481
00:34:06.019 --> 00:34:07.819
- Can't I come?
- Stay.

482
00:34:10.019 --> 00:34:11.339
Nice car.

483
00:34:11.899 --> 00:34:13.739
- What are you doing?
- Hooking it up.

484
00:34:14.019 --> 00:34:16.019
You're not being careful!

485
00:34:16.299 --> 00:34:18.739
I know what I'm doing. It's a car...

486
00:34:18.899 --> 00:34:20.259
...not a baby carriage.

487
00:34:20.499 --> 00:34:22.739
You're chipping the paint.

488
00:34:23.859 --> 00:34:26.700
- You smell what I smell?
- I smell it.

489
00:34:26.940 --> 00:34:28.340
A rat?

490
00:34:28.940 --> 00:34:30.740
A real stinky one.

491
00:34:34.380 --> 00:34:35.580
Where you going?

492
00:34:35.860 --> 00:34:40.100
I'm a peeping Tom. It goes
with the badge. It's fun sometimes.

493
00:34:42.380 --> 00:34:43.460
Bingo!

494
00:34:47.300 --> 00:34:48.940
Lars, look!

495
00:34:49.220 --> 00:34:50.260
What the fuck?!

496
00:34:55.740 --> 00:34:56.980
Where's the pool?

497
00:34:57.220 --> 00:34:58.200
No pool.

498
00:34:58.300 --> 00:35:01.380
- Of course there is.
- This house is built on stilts.

499
00:35:01.580 --> 00:35:03.741
I'm sure there's a pool.

500
00:35:15.461 --> 00:35:16.861
Cuff yourselves.

501
00:35:44.662 --> 00:35:46.022
Move that truck!

502
00:35:47.622 --> 00:35:48.782
Your keys!

503
00:35:51.142 --> 00:35:52.342
You all right?

504
00:35:53.182 --> 00:35:54.262
Where you going?

505
00:35:54.462 --> 00:35:55.942
That was the waiter from the hotel.

506
00:35:56.102 --> 00:35:57.182
Wait for me!

507
00:35:57.502 --> 00:35:58.942
Get the fuck out of here!

508
00:35:59.182 --> 00:36:01.862
What are you doing?!
You can't take my truck!

509
00:36:16.382 --> 00:36:18.823
Sergeant, it's the guy from the hotel!

510
00:36:18.983 --> 00:36:20.303
Where did he go?

511
00:36:20.703 --> 00:36:23.023
Riggs is hanging on the truck!

512
00:36:23.223 --> 00:36:26.543
What are you doing out of the car?
